# lodor#7 disc-1-first: a POPULATED .m3u whose disc 2 is a 0-byte stub is the designed
# partial state (the stub gate can't see it — the m3u isn't a stub). The hook must fire
# --fetch-next-disc, the disc lands, and the launch proceeds (exit 0).
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): populated .m3u + stub disc 2 -> --fetch-next-disc lands it
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u	FF7/D1.chd\nFF7/D2.chd\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D1.chd
sdfile Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT fetched=1 complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_file_has Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd	DISCBYTES
